title: Breast Feeding Initiation, United Kingdom, 2007/08
name: Breast Feeding Initiation, United Kingdom, 2007/08
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on breast feeding initiation. Breast feeding has well known health benefits for the child and for the mother in later life. It costs nothing to implement and should be amenable to change through public health intervention.The percentage of women giving birth in 2007/08 who put their baby to the breast in the first 48 hours after delivery, out of all maternities where breast feeding initiation status is recorded.
